## Context
SwipeablePromptCard has powerful swipe gestures (left to copy, right to basket) that users never discover because there's no visual indication they exist.

## Proposed Solution

### 1. First-Card Hint Overlay
Show a one-time hint on the first prompt card:

```tsx
// SwipeHint.tsx
export function SwipeHint({ onDismiss }: { onDismiss: () => void }) {
  return (
    <motion.div
      initial={{ opacity: 0 }}
      animate={{ opacity: 1 }}
      exit={{ opacity: 0 }}
      className="absolute inset-0 z-20 flex items-center justify-center bg-black/60 rounded-xl backdrop-blur-sm"
    >
      <div className="text-center text-white px-6">
        <div className="flex items-center justify-center gap-8 mb-4">
          {/* Left swipe indicator */}
          <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
            <ArrowLeft className="w-5 h-5 animate-pulse" />
            <span className="text-sm font-medium">Copy</span>
          </div>

          {/* Right swipe indicator */}
          <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
            <span className="text-sm font-medium">Basket</span>
            <ArrowRight className="w-5 h-5 animate-pulse" />
          </div>
        </div>

        <p className="text-xs text-white/70 mb-4">
          Swipe cards for quick actions
        </p>

        <Button
          size="sm"
          variant="secondary"
          onClick={onDismiss}
          className="text-xs"
        >
          Got it
        </Button>
      </div>
    </motion.div>
  );
}
```

### 2. Persist Dismissal in localStorage
```tsx
const SWIPE_HINT_KEY = "jfp-swipe-hint-dismissed";

function useSwipeHint() {
  const [showHint, setShowHint] = useLocalStorage(SWIPE_HINT_KEY, true);

  const dismissHint = useCallback(() => {
    setShowHint(false);
  }, [setShowHint]);

  return { showHint, dismissHint };
}
```

### 3. Integration in SwipeablePromptCard
```tsx
export function SwipeablePromptCard({ prompt, index, ...props }) {
  const { showHint, dismissHint } = useSwipeHint();
  const shouldShowHint = showHint && index === 0; // Only first card

  return (
    <div className="relative">
      <PromptCard ... />

      <AnimatePresence>
        {shouldShowHint && isMobile && (
          <SwipeHint onDismiss={dismissHint} />
        )}
      </AnimatePresence>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### 4. Subtle Edge Indicators (Alternative/Additional)
Add permanent but subtle visual cues on card edges:

```tsx
{/* Left edge - Copy hint */}
<div className="absolute left-0 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-1 h-12 rounded-r-full bg-sky-400/30" />

{/* Right edge - Basket hint */}
<div className="absolute right-0 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-1 h-12 rounded-l-full bg-indigo-400/30" />
```

## Design Rationale
- One-time overlay: Teaches without being annoying
- "Got it" button: Gives user control
- localStorage persistence: Never shows again
- Only first card: Minimal disruption
- Edge indicators (optional): Permanent subtle hints

